Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{120}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @British beef mince{120} and @British smoked bacon lardons{60}. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Remove from the heat, then stir through the @BBQ sauce{32}.

Pop your @pizza bases{2} onto a #cutting board{}. Spread the @marinara sauce{120} over the pizza bases, leaving a 1cm border around the edge. Top with the BBQ beef and bacon, then layer on the @chorizo slices{50}. Scatter the cheese over the top.

When the oven is hot, slide the pizzas directly onto the middle rack and bake until the base is golden and the cheese is melted and bubbling, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Rocket Side Salad ==

Just before the pizzas are ready, pop the @wild rocket{40} and remaining @baby plum tomatoes{} into a #medium bowl{}. Drizzle with the @olive oil{} for the dressing and toss to dress. Finish with a drizzle of @balsamic vinegar{12}.

== To Serve ==

When the pizzas are ready, pop onto a #serving board{} and cut into slices. Serve up your ultimate meat lover's cheesy pizza with the rocket side salad in a #bowl{} alongside. Enjoy!